SIMPLE: initial
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Initial
<hw>In*i"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>initialis</ets>, from <ets>initium</ets> a going in, entrance,
beginning, fr. <ets>inire</ets> to go into, to enter, begin; pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>ire</ets> to go: cf. F. <ets>initial</ets>. See
<er>Issue</er>, and cf. <er>Commence</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the beginning; marking the
commencement; incipient; commencing; <as>as, the <ex>initial</ex>
symptoms of a disease</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Placed at the beginning; standing at the head, as of
a list or series; <as>as, the <ex>initial</ex> letters of a
name</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Initial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Initial
<hw>In*i"tial</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The first letter of a word or a
name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Initial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Initial
<hw>In*i"tial</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Initialed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Initialing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To put an initial to; to mark
with an initial of initials.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>initialise</ent>⟦br⟧
